article.headline: Florida State overcomes slow start for 7th win in row
article.linkText: Florida State overcomes slow start for 7th win in row
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Al Thornton scored 14 points and Florida State overcame a slow start to beat St. Peter's 76-63 on Saturday, the Seminoles' seventh straight win. St. Peter's (3-8) dominated the interior, outrebounding the Seminoles 42-25, but struggled with Florida State's depth. The Seminoles had a 29-13 edge in bench scoring. Isaiah Swann had 12 points for the Seminoles, Ralph Mims and Casaan Breeden each added 11,and Jason Rich had 10. Florida State (11-2) did not make its first basket until the 14:21 mark in the first half, but used runs of 9-0 and 10-1 to take a 40-31 halftime lead. Thornton scored 12 of points in the opening half. The Peacocks had 25 turnovers and struggled from outside, making 1-of-11 shots from 3-point range. Todd Sowell had a game-high 21 points for St. Peter's, along with 11 rebounds for his sixth double-double this season. The Peacocks also got 15 points from Raul Orta and 13 from Akeem Gooding.
